The paper deals with the task of recognizing operation phases in endoscopic videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of classification models and temporal smoothing methods, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the use of a Hidden Markov Model to model the sequence of predictions, which is a technique commonly used in information retrieval. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
